attachments.text:
Closes <https://github.com/coronasafe/care_fe/issues/2141|#2141>

`pulse` and `ventilator_spo2` are casted to `Number`. This means that in cases where they are left blank, they are actually forced to be stored as 0, rather than null. ( `Number(null) -> 0` ) Which causes the above issue. Removing this cast resolves it. `null` values displayed properly as `-` in the charts and not as 0s.

Fixes <https://github.com/coronasafe/care_fe/issues/3614|#3614>

*Proposed Changes*

• This PR improves how data is re-fetched. Instead of using window reload, (which reloads the entire page) we now use proper fetchData functions to refresh and present the new data to the user without reloading the entire page.

Places where this has changed: (Notice how the notifications stay on the page instead of immediately getting lost on a page reload)

1. Allocating a bed  
    <https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3626859/192108243-826e1763-5c52-4979-be86-eb64900ab1ed.png|image>
2. Deleting users  
    <https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3626859/192108298-fe2d0c04-6305-4042-a699-52308316ec0c.png|image>
3. Inventory Log  
    <https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3626859/192108371-6221cd0b-7cf0-47de-8d0d-df4131412ad2.png|image>
